div.div: Ok app. Seems to track runs well enough, although the current pace indicator often seems way off. Do like the live tracking for security on long runs, but much preferred the Nike+ running front summary page with quickest time for several standard distances. Find MMR a little cumbersome outside of actually tracking a run. Needs work on collecting unique badges, trophies etc...for you efforts.
Enjoying it. More stable now.

div.strong: Does what I need it to do

div.div: Like tracking the splits
When it works, it's great. Have now had a handful of times where I start the workout, lock my phone, and then when I go to pause or end my workout...the app shows I've gone 0.1 miles.

div.strong: I want to delete certain workouts

div.div: It's a great app but I won't let you delete work outs
I have liked the app but a couple of times it tracked the wrong route and time. Not sure where it went wrong. When it does that I have to delete the workout because it screws up my summary.
This app is great but the music stops right in the middle of a workout! Very frustrating
Definitely a useful app, but too many features are premium-only.
I have found this app to be unreliable. When it works it is great.

div.strong: Useful app with a few issues.

div.div: GPS is pretty accurate but killer on your battery life (to be expected). The app should be able to integrate with other music apps (Spotify, pandora etc). It annoyingly starts Apple music every time you begin a work out. Turn by turn would be nice for longer or new planned routes. Icon is kind of silly. And I know Under armour sponsors the app but it is all over the interior of the app, does it need to be on the icon?
I like the app fine when it works, but every other upgrade is buggy. This time the controls for music are gone.

This app meets my low expectations. Marks time and distance, tracks elevation. Lacks good map data: won't plot across some railroad bridges, creek bridges. Annoyingly, asks for feedback after every run.
I am using this app a lot when I run and so far it is great. I have only had 2 problems with the music streaming while I run and with the other app my fitness pal taking over occasionally.

div.strong: Works great outside. Can't figure out how to make it work on the track inside.

div.div: The app works awesome outside when running/walking around a neighborhood/park/etc. But when I have to use it on a track (inside or outside) it gets totally confused!!
So far use to get splits for mile and compare to other runs. Verbal time is great because can't see phone without bifocals. Will see if blue tooth pulse meter works while using blue tooth headset
Hi
Very helpful

A lot of good thinking went into this ap. It will reliably "Map your Run, Ride" or whatever. Two major issues are 1) no mile splits shown on run/ride graphics depicting heart rate, altitude etc, and 2) no way other than manual enter to record treadmill workouts.
There are times the mileage is off, but not enough for me to not use the app. Used it for years and love it!

div.strong: Good app with room for improvement

div.div: Better than the other 2 running apps I've tried. I wish I could put in a goal for a particular run. I like the split times it provides.

Good iPhone app lots of nice features, for the free portion, and if you pay extra if you get some more options that are necessary but fun. However the watch app does not update I continuously, the time you're exercising when using OTHER it locks up even though the app is still running on the iPhone

So far so good, except for it autopauses when I'm still running sometimes. I know I'm slow but come on now! I also can't figure out how to sync it with MyFitnessPal. Only gives me options to sync bike times which is weird because I don't use it for anything but running.
I like the app, but I wish it would tell you half mile splits as well as mile splits.

UA has simply done a wonderful job with this app. Routes, social posting, very customizable, tracking capabilities, data compilation and analysis - everything works great.
The optional heart-rate monitor is inconsistent - too many bugs to list. Until they fix the bugs to make it reliable, I'll stick with the old Polar.

div.strong: Works fine for the most part

div.div: Like the way it tracks time, distance, and I assume the calorie counter is accurate. The music skipped to the next track 3 times while in the middle of a song. The screen was locked so I don't know why it does that. The notification at the mile markers goes on way too long.

div.strong: Great but, spotify is way ahead

div.div: Love the app, but the app needs a tempo monitor like spotify, music matches my pace. Able to run way longer with spotify playing in the background.
Good layout easy to use even wit a dog in hand
The app works well if you are keeping your app open on the screen and your phone unlocked. If you close the screen the app jumps mileage and calories. It becomes extremely inaccurate.
Works well but can't stand the ads
Good app just reviewing so it stops asking me to review
App works really well! Been having problems lately with posting workouts to Facebook though.

div.strong: Lose GPS at times but like the app

div.div: I have used this app more than 10 times. 3 of the 10 have lost GPS route and given a wrong report. I run the same route at the same time so I know pretty much what I should be at. It is frustrating but not the end of the world.
Track went well
I use it for power walking. Pace and distance is off sometimes. Maybe because I use a windy, wooded path around a lake.
The app works fine, but I hate the way it always assumes my workout was a "walk" when I finish. News flash: some people run 9 minute miles and it's unmotivating for the app to downgrade my hard work.

MapMyRun worked great with my three year-old HTC Evo. Now with a new iPhone 6 the GPS tracking is not accurate. On my last run MMR told me I had hit the six mile mark but I knew I was only at about five miles. The tracking hasn’t been accurate a single time since I got this new phone about five weeks ago.

div.strong: I don't want to share, thank you

div.div: This is a great app but I don't care to share my run on Facebook, I do it for my own pleasure. Quit trying to force me to post on social media.

div.strong: Good App, Needs a few improvements

div.div: Love this for tracking runs, hikes and biking. I would like to be able to tag people though so we don't both have to carry our phones. The calories are also way off and could do a better job based on height, weight, etc.

div.strong: I really don't know I'm new to all this....

div.div: I'll have more to say after I use it more often.

div.strong: Lot of new features but still lacking

div.div: They've added too many features and the app doesn't seem as stable and precise.

div.strong: Indoor options would help in winter

div.div: I walk-run 4 to 5 times per week. I am 54 years old and like to keep up on my exercise before and after work. I can't always run outside due to weather so I'm glad there's a walk treadmill option but it doesn't work at all on the elliptical or stationary bike. I have to edit for miles and calories to add them in.
Same route only added .2 of a mile but didn't register making my route longer ran farther and time is about the same... Weird!!
Love the app. It never correctly counts calories burned, which is a big reason why I use the app and a heart rate monitor.
Love it!!! Super easy to use. Has every feature I could want. But the advertisements and tactics to get me to give them money are annoying

Just learning how to use app need more time. Like it so far.
So far so good. I like the prompting of every mile and that you can play music.
Wish there were more voice prompts!

div.strong: An app good for movement on foot.

div.div: Please try to improve the bike options. Don't see anything for hybrid bikes or for casual paseo riding.
